{
    "name": "Sage",
    "type": "npc",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Sage",
            "type": "section",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 241",
                        "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 241",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                    },
                    "page": 241
                }
            ],
            "html": "The greatest knowledge comes from experience. Village elders, ancient seers, and advisors to royalty are examples of individuals who are valued for their experiences. Sages serve their people as much as their sovereigns. They educate and try to prevent their people from straying from their cultures' acceptable norms and traditions. Sages rarely take power for themselves, as they take their responsibility seriously to guide wisely and empower those they serve.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Humanoid</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"14\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Society</a></u>)</b>: DC 22"
        },
        {
            "name": "Scholars",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Centers Of Learning",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 240",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 240",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 240
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "locations",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Locations",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Locations",
                        "image": "Sidebar_3_Locations.png"
                    },
                    "html": ""
                },
                {
                    "name": "Kitharodian Academy (Taldor)",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 240",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 240",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 240
                        }
                    ],
                    "html": ": Famed bardic college teaching students of all social classes. <br/><b>Magaambya (Nantambu)</b>: Ancient school with some of the world's greatest stores of arcane knowledge. <br/><b>University of Lepidstadt (Ustalav)</b>: School primarily focusing on alchemy, medicine, and scientific study."
                },
                {
                    "name": "Uncommon Scholastic Disciplines",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 240",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 240",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 240
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    },
                    "html": "Beside the life and natural sciences such as arcana, biology, botany, geology, oceanography, and zoology, demand is increasing in cities for more modern disciplines, like anthropology, economics, sociology, urban planning, and even art curation and forensic investigation."
                }
            ],
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 240",
                        "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 240",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                    },
                    "page": 240
                }
            ],
            "html": "True power comes from knowledge: the power to shape the growth of kingdoms by mere whispers, staying three steps ahead of adversaries, or even knowing which flora is best for creating untraceable poisons."
        }
    ],
